# Clean code standards

- Keep implementations minimal; remove dead code and unreachable branches you touch.
- No unused imports/variables; run/resolve lints for edited files.
- Keep functions/components small and purpose-driven (SRP).
- Prefer explicit, readable naming over cleverness.
- Do not introduce secrets into the repo (.env, credentials).
- When asked to add temporary test code/files, remove them after verification.
